Project Overview
=================

1) Project Map & Responsibilities
- Backend (Flask)
  • backend/app.py: Flask entrypoint, registers blueprints, CORS.
  • backend/routes/credibility_routes.py: API endpoints /api/parse_internship_info, /api/verify_company, /api/predict, /api/extract_url_features; lazy initializes services.
  • backend/services/info_parser.py: Parses raw internship text into structured fields (company, position, salary, duration, work type, red flags, jobDescription).
  • backend/services/company_verifier.py: Heuristic online presence/scam checks; scores safety; platform indicators.
  • backend/services/credibility_engine.py: Final weighted credibility scoring (company verification, URL, email, sentiment, parsed-data quality, red-flag penalty); recommendations.
  • backend/services/url_feature_extractor.py: URL safety features (https, hyphens, digits, entropy).
  • backend/services/sentiment_analyzer.py: TextBlob sentiment wrapper (fallback neutral).
  • backend/preprocessing/text_cleaner.py: Basic text cleaning for sentiment.
  • Models (optional): backend/models/random_forest_inference.py, backend/models/text_cnn_inference.py expect saved models under backend/models/saved/; if missing, heuristics still run.

- Frontend (Static HTML/CSS/JS)
  • Pages: frontend/pages/check.html (single textarea input, resume vs JD validator), analysis.html (calls backend parse + predict), result.html (shows scores), plus about/contact/etc.
  • Core JS: frontend/js/core/navigation.js (navigation, storage), storage.js (localStorage helpers), validation.js (form validation).
  • Analysis JS: frontend/js/analysis/analysis.js (legacy local scoring fallback), resume.js (resume↔JD matching; keyword fallback, HF embeddings if key set), result.js (render result cards).
  • Config: frontend/js/config/config.js (CONFIG.API_BASE_URL, optional HF_API_KEY).
  • Assets/CSS: frontend/css/** layouts, components, animations.

- Scripts & Utilities
  • frontend/scripts/serve_frontend.py: Simple static server (port 8000 default).
  • backend/scripts/smoke_tests.py, backend/scripts/check_imports.py: Quick checks.
  • frontend/scripts/update_paths.ps1: Path utilities.
  • Tests: tests/run_tests.py, tests/integration/test_api_integration.py, etc.

- Datasets/Loaders
  • backend/datasets/huggingface_loader.py, backend/datasets/kaggle_loader.py: Helpers/stubs for dataset loading (not required at runtime).

2) Dependencies to Install
- Python backend (from project root):
  pip install -r backend/requirements.txt
  Key libs: Flask, flask-cors, requests, python-dotenv, tldextract, url-normalize, whois, beautifulsoup4, nltk, textblob, joblib.
- Frontend: plain HTML/CSS/JS (no npm build needed).
- Optional: Hugging Face Inference API key (set HF_API_KEY in frontend/js/config/config.js or localStorage hf_api_key) for resume↔JD semantic matching.

3) Run Commands (PowerShell, from project root)
- Activate venv (if not already):
  .\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
- Start backend:
  .\.venv\Scripts\python.exe backend\app.py
  Serves at http://localhost:5000 (API base http://localhost:5000/api)
- Start frontend:
  .\.venv\Scripts\python.exe frontend\scripts\serve_frontend.py
  Serves at http://localhost:8000
- Optional tests:
  .\.venv\Scripts\python.exe tests\run_tests.py

4) Feature Flow (simplified)
- User enters raw internship info on Check page (single textarea; optional JD/resume paste).
- Frontend calls /api/parse_internship_info to extract structured fields.
- Frontend calls /api/predict with parsed data → backend credibility_engine combines: company verification, URL/email checks, sentiment, parsed-data quality, red-flag penalty.
- Results rendered on Result page; resume vs JD match uses keyword overlap or HF embeddings if key is present.

5) Notes
- If you see “Model not found at models/saved/random_forest.pkl”, it’s informational; heuristics still run.
- Resume/JD validation: ensure both textareas have content; HF key optional; keyword fallback works without it.
- If backend port is busy, stop old python processes or change port in backend/app.py.
